quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  69,9,"And Pharaoh, and those before him, and the cities overthrown, committed habitual, harmful deeds"
  69,10,"And they did not follow the messenger of their Lord, so He punished them with a sufficient penalty"
  69,11,"We, when the water overflowed beyond its limits, carried you in the Ark"
  69,12,"That We might make it a message for you, and that ears which hear the tale retain it to memory, and bear its lessons in mind"
  69,13,Then when a single trumpet is blown
  69,14,"And the earth and its mountains are moved, and they are crushed to powder with a single pound"
  69,15,On that day will the Event come to pass
  69,16,"And the universe will be rent asunder, for it will be flimsy that day"
  69,17,"And the angels will be on its sides, and eight will that day, bear the throne of your Lord above them"
  69,18,That day you will be brought to Judgment. Not an act of yours that you hide will be hidden
  69,19,"Then he, who will be given his record in his right hand will say, “Ah here, read my record"
  69,20,“I indeed understood that my account would reach me.”
  69,21,And he will be in a life of bliss
  69,22,In a garden on high
  69,23,Fruits hanging low and near
  69,24,"“Eat and drink with full satisfaction, because of that which you sent before you, in days gone by.”"
  69,25,"And he who will be given his record in his left hand will say, “I wish that my record had not been given to me"
  69,26,“And that I had never realized how my account stood
  69,27,“I wish that death had been the end of me
  69,28,“Of no profit to me is my wealth
  69,29,“My power has vanished from me.”
  69,30,"Then it will be said, “Seize him and bind him"
  69,31,“And burn him in the blazing fire
  69,32,"“Further, make him march in a chain-gang, with a length of seventy cubits"
  69,33,"“This was he who would not believe in God, Most High"
  69,34,“And would not encourage the feeding of the indigent